    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rollback Runbooks for GenAI Services"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A rollback runbook is a step-by-step procedure that an on-call engineer can execute under pressure, in the middle of the night, without ambiguity about what to do next. The goal is to reduce the time from detection to stable-version-restored to under 7 minutes \u2014 a target that is only achievable if the runbook is written before the incident, tested before go-live, and kept current as the system evolves."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GenAI services have four distinct rollback targets that do not appear in conventional web services: the feature flag routing the canary, the prompt template version, the LLM model version, and the service container image. Each has a different execution path, speed, and risk profile. The runbook must cover all four and specify which one to use given the symptoms."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Rollback runbook: 5-step flow (Detect \u2192 Triage \u2192 Rollback \u2192 Verify \u2192 Communicate) with target 7-minute recovery time. Four rollback types: Feature Flag (<30s), Prompt Template (1-2min), LLM Model Version (2-5min), Service Image (3-8min). Post-rollback verification checklist shows eval pass rate, error rate, P99 latency, safety flags, feature flag confirmed 0%, incident opened."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Runbook Structure and Principles"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A good runbook has five properties: it is executable by any on-call engineer (not just the feature author), every step has a concrete command or check, decision points have explicit criteria (not 'use your judgment'), it includes verification steps after each action, and it is version-controlled alongside the feature it covers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The runbook is not a postmortem template or an architecture document. It does not explain why the system works the way it does \u2014 that belongs in the design doc. It tells the on-call engineer exactly what to run and what to look for, in order, when the alert fires at 3am."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Write the runbook as a dry run first: have an engineer who did not author the feature execute each step in staging before the production rollout. Any step that requires outside knowledge or judgment becomes a gap to fix."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rollback Type 1: Feature Flag (Canary Routing)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The fastest and lowest-risk rollback. If the GenAI feature is gated behind a feature flag that controls canary routing, disabling the flag immediately redirects all traffic back to the stable version. No deployment required."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Canary rollout triggered the rollback (eval, safety, latency, or error rate breach during ring advancement)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The new version is functionally broken \u2014 returning errors or malformed responses \u2014 and users need relief immediately."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The cause is unknown and you need time to investigate without ongoing user impact."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Execution"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Rollback: Feature flag (LaunchDarkly)\n# 1. Disable the canary flag immediately\nlaunchdarkly-cli flag set \\\n  --flag genai-assistant-v2 \\\n  --value false \\\n  --comment \"rollback: $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) \u2014 on-call: $ONCALL_NAME\"\n\n# 2. Verify the flag is now false\nlaunchdarkly-cli flag get --flag genai-assistant-v2 | grep '\"value\"'\n# Expected output: \"value\": false\n\n# 3. Confirm canary traffic dropped to zero (allow 60s for cache expiry)\nsleep 60\ncurl -s \"https://prometheus.internal/api/v1/query?query=\\\n  rate(genai_requests_total{slot='canary'}[2m])\" \\\n  | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); \\\n    print('canary_rps:', d['data']['result'][0]['value'][1] if d['data']['result'] else '0 (none)')\"\n# Expected: 0 or empty result\n\n# 4. Confirm stable version is serving all traffic\ncurl -s \"https://prometheus.internal/api/v1/query?query=\\\n  rate(genai_requests_total{slot='stable'}[2m])\" \\\n  | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); \\\n    print('stable_rps:', d['data']['result'][0]['value'][1])\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rollback Type 2: Prompt Template Version"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt templates are typically stored in a config file, database row, or a versioned store (e.g., a Git-backed config repo or AWS AppConfig). Rolling back a prompt template means pinning the service back to the previous version identifier without redeploying the service binary."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Eval pass rate dropped after a prompt template change, and the LLM model and service image are unchanged."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Responses show a structural regression (wrong JSON schema, changed output format) that matches a recent prompt edit."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Safety flag rate increased after a prompt template change."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Execution"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Rollback: Prompt template version (example using AWS AppConfig)\n\n# 1. List recent prompt template deployments\naws appconfig list-deployed-configurations \\\n  --application genai-assistant \\\n  --environment production \\\n  --query 'Items[?ConfigurationProfileId==`prompt-template`].{Version:VersionNumber,DeployedAt:DeploymentDurationInMinutes}' \\\n  --output table\n\n# 2. Identify the last-known-good version number (from the table above)\nSTABLE_VERSION=42   # replace with actual version from output\n\n# 3. Roll back to the stable version\naws appconfig start-deployment \\\n  --application genai-assistant \\\n  --environment production \\\n  --deployment-strategy AllAtOnce \\\n  --configuration-profile-id prompt-template \\\n  --configuration-version $STABLE_VERSION \\\n  --description \"rollback to v${STABLE_VERSION}: on-call rollback $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\"\n\n# 4. Verify the active configuration version\naws appconfig get-deployed-configuration \\\n  --application genai-assistant \\\n  --environment production \\\n  --configuration prompt-template \\\n  --client-id rollback-verify-$(date +%s) \\\n  --client-configuration-version 0 \\\n  /tmp/prompt_check.txt\ncat /tmp/prompt_check.txt | python3 -m json.tool | head -5\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rollback Type 3: LLM Model Version"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the GenAI service is pinned to a specific LLM model version via an environment variable or config value, rolling back means changing that value and triggering a rolling restart of the service pods. This takes 2\u20135 minutes because pods must restart and warm up."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Eval quality or safety regression coincides with an LLM provider model version change (e.g., OpenAI auto-upgraded to a new gpt-4o snapshot)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "P99 latency increased and the LLM model was changed between the stable and canary versions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The prompt template and service image are unchanged, ruling out those as causes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Execution"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Rollback: LLM model version (Kubernetes + environment variable)\n\n# 1. Check current model version in the canary deployment\nkubectl get deployment genai-api-canary -n production \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].env[?(@.name==\"LLM_MODEL\")].value}'\n# Example output: gpt-4o-2024-08-06\n\n# 2. Identify the stable model version\nkubectl get deployment genai-api-stable -n production \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].env[?(@.name==\"LLM_MODEL\")].value}'\n# Example output: gpt-4o-2024-05-13\n\nSTABLE_MODEL=\"gpt-4o-2024-05-13\"  # replace with output above\n\n# 3. Patch the canary deployment to use the stable model version\nkubectl set env deployment/genai-api-canary \\\n  LLM_MODEL=$STABLE_MODEL \\\n  -n production\n\n# 4. Watch the rolling restart\nkubectl rollout status deployment/genai-api-canary -n production --timeout=5m\n# Wait until: \"deployment successfully rolled out\"\n\n# 5. Verify model version in running pods\nkubectl get pods -n production -l app=genai-api,slot=canary \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.items[0].spec.containers[0].env[?(@.name==\"LLM_MODEL\")].value}'\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rollback Type 4: Service Container Image"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A full image rollback reverts the service container to the previous tagged image. This handles regressions in application code (not model or prompt), such as a broken parser, a changed output schema, or a dependency version conflict. It requires a full rolling deployment, which takes 3\u20138 minutes depending on cluster size and readiness probe timing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "HTTP error rate spiked and the canary logs show application exceptions (not LLM API errors)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A downstream service is rejecting the canary's response format due to a changed serialization layer."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Model and prompt are unchanged; the regression is in application code deployed with this image."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Execution"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Rollback: Service container image (Kubernetes)\n\n# 1. Check current image tag in production\nkubectl get deployment genai-api -n production \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}'\n# Example output: 123456789.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/genai-api:v2.5.1\n\n# 2. Roll back to previous revision using kubectl rollout undo\nkubectl rollout undo deployment/genai-api -n production\n\n# 3. Alternatively, specify an explicit revision number\n# First, list available revisions:\nkubectl rollout history deployment/genai-api -n production\n# Then roll back to a specific revision:\nkubectl rollout undo deployment/genai-api -n production --to-revision=14\n\n# 4. Watch the rollout\nkubectl rollout status deployment/genai-api -n production --timeout=8m\n\n# 5. Confirm the image tag after rollback\nkubectl get deployment genai-api -n production \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}'\n\n# 6. Verify pods are running the rolled-back image\nkubectl get pods -n production -l app=genai-api \\\n  -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
