      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/post_rollback_verify.sh \u2014 run after any rollback\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\nPROM=\"https://prometheus.internal/api/v1/query\"\n\nquery() { curl -sG \"$PROM\" --data-urlencode \"query=$1\" | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nr=d['data']['result']\nprint(r[0]['value'][1] if r else '0')\n\"; }\n\necho \"=== Post-Rollback Verification ===\"\necho \"\"\n\ncanary_rps=$(query \"rate(genai_requests_total{slot='canary'}[2m])\")\necho \"Canary RPS:   $canary_rps  (target: 0)\"\n\nerror_rate=$(query \"rate(genai_http_errors_total{slot='stable'}[5m])\")\necho \"Error rate:   $error_rate  (target: \u2264 baseline)\"\n\np99=$(query \"histogram_quantile(0.99, rate(genai_request_duration_seconds_bucket{slot='stable'}[5m]))\")\necho \"P99 latency:  ${p99}s  (target: \u2264 2.0s)\"\n\nsafety_rate=$(query \"rate(genai_safety_flags_total[5m]) / rate(genai_requests_total[5m])\")\necho \"Safety flags: $safety_rate  (target: \u2264 0.0005)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"Running spot eval (30 cases)...\"\npython3 scripts/spot_eval.py --env production --sample 30\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Communication Template"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "During a rollback, the on-call engineer must post status updates to the incident channel within 5 minutes of detection, at rollback completion, and after verification. This keeps stakeholders informed and prevents escalation based on silence."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Incident channel message \u2014 Detection (T+0 to T+2 min)\n\ud83d\udd34 INCIDENT [genai-assistant]: Rollback in progress\n- Trigger: [eval pass rate dropped to 86% / canary error rate 2.1% / safety spike]\n- Impact: [~N% of users on canary cohort seeing degraded responses]\n- Action: Executing feature flag rollback to stable version\n- ETA to stable: ~2 minutes\n- On-call: @name | Incident: #inc-YYYYMMDD-001\n\n# Incident channel message \u2014 Rollback complete (T+7 min)\n\u2705 ROLLBACK COMPLETE [genai-assistant]\n- Stable version restored: 100% traffic on genai-api:v2.4\n- Canary traffic: 0 RPS confirmed\n- Eval pass rate: 96.2% (restored to baseline)\n- Error rate: 0.04% (restored to baseline)\n- Incident remains open for root cause investigation\n- On-call continuing investigation\n\n# Incident channel message \u2014 All-clear (T+30 min)\n\u2705 ALL CLEAR [genai-assistant]\n- Stable version confirmed healthy for 30 minutes\n- Root cause: [brief description or \"under investigation\"]\n- Next steps: post-mortem scheduled for [date/time]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Keeping the Runbook Current"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A runbook that is 3 months out of date is worse than no runbook \u2014 it gives false confidence and may execute the wrong commands against a system that has changed. Maintain the rollback runbook alongside the deployment automation, and enforce review at specific checkpoints."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Any change to the feature flag name, LaunchDarkly project, or routing mechanism requires a runbook update before the change ships."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Any change to the LLM model version variable name, the prompt template store, or the Kubernetes deployment names requires a runbook update."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run a dry-run of the runbook in staging once per quarter, or after any significant infrastructure change."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Include the runbook URL in the PagerDuty incident payload so the on-call engineer has it immediately when paged."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add a 'last validated' date to the runbook header and fail the go/no-go checklist if it is more than 90 days old."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A rollback runbook for a GenAI service covers four targets \u2014 feature flag, prompt template, LLM model version, and service image \u2014 each with different execution speed and risk. The runbook must be written, tested in staging, and linked from the PagerDuty alert before go-live. After execution, post-rollback verification runs specific metric checks before the incident can be downgraded. The communication template ensures stakeholders receive timely updates without the on-call engineer needing to compose messages while also executing the rollback. The runbook must be updated whenever routing, model, prompt, or deployment infrastructure changes."
          }
        ]
      }
